				p.cont-fs #[strong Here at myTEFL.net, we take your privacy very seriously. If you have further questions regarding our privacy policy, email us at #[a(href="#") admin@mytefl.net.] ] #[br]#[br]#[strong Statement on Cookies]  #[br]#[br]MyTEFL uses cookies to enable various features and functionality and we are changing the information we provide to make it easier for you to see how we use cookies while visiting our site.#[br]#[br]#[strong About Cookies]#[br]#[br]Cookies are small text files placed on your computer by us, or our partners. They let us identify the device you're using - but they never identify you personally. This information is sent back to our systems as you move around our website.#[br]#[br]Cookies are unique to the web browser you're using - so if you're using a desktop computer as well as a mobile, different data will be collected for each.#[br]#[br]Cookies can be set by the owner of the website you're on. These are known as 1st Party Cookies. There are also 3rd Party Cookies that can be set by partner websites. Only the owner of the cookie can see the anonymous information it collects.#[br]#[br]#[strong Refusing cookies]#[br]#[br]You can change your browser settings by clicking on the help feature, to accept or refuse all cookies, choose which cookies you want or don't want, or ask to be notified when a cookie is set. It is important to note that if you refuse some cookies then you will not benefit from all the features and functionality available on this website.#[br]#[br]#[strong What information do we collect?]#[br]#[br]We collect information from you when you register on our site, place an order or fill out a form.#[br]#[br]When ordering or registering on our site, as appropriate, you may be asked to enter your: name, e-mail address, mailing address, phone number or credit card information. You may, however, visit our site anonymous#[br]#[br]#[strong What do we use your information for?]#[br]#[br]Any of the information we collect from you may be used in one of the following ways:
				br
